1. ABSTRACT

Diabetes is a chronic metabolic disorder that is marked by high blood glucose levels. The early diagnosis of diabetes can go a long way in lowering the risks associated with it and improving patient outcomes. The objective of this project is to analyze medical data and build a machine learning model to predict the possibility of a patient having diabetes using medical measurements. Logistic Regression was used as the main classification algorithm. The results showed that the accuracy of the model was satisfactory and that glucose levels and BMI are crucial in determining diabetes.

2. INTRODUCTION

Healthcare analytics is an important area in disease prediction and preventive medicine. With the growing availability of medical data, machine learning can help in early diagnosis.

The project aims to predict diabetes based on patient health records. By using exploratory data analysis and classification techniques, we can try to find important medical factors related to diabetes.

3. PROBLEM STATEMENT

The problem statement for this project is to develop a predictive model that will classify patients as either diabetic or non-diabetic based on medical attributes.

Target Variable:

0 → Non-Diabetic

1 → Diabetic

Objective:

Analyze dataset

Extract important health attributes

Develop classification model

Test model performance

4. DATASET DESCRIPTION

The dataset used for this project is based on the Pima Indians Diabetes Dataset found on Kaggle.

Attributes:

Pregnancies – Number of times pregnant

Glucose – Plasma glucose concentration

BloodPressure – Diastolic blood pressure (mm Hg)

SkinThickness – Triceps skin fold thickness (mm)

Insulin – 2-Hour serum insulin (mu U/ml)

BMI – Body Mass Index

DiabetesPedigreeFunction – Genetic likelihood of diabetes

Age – Age of patient

Outcome – Target variable (0 or 1)

5. TOOLS AND TECHNOLOGIES USED

Python

Jupyter Notebook

